Question 1: Class Definition

Define a Python class named Rectangle. This class should have:

Two attributes: length (float) and width (float).
A method named area() that calculates and returns the area of the rectangle.
Create an instance of the Rectangle class with a length of 5.0 units and a width of 3.0 units. Print the area of the rectangle using the area() method.

Question 2: Object Initialization

Define a Python class named Person. This class should have:

Two attributes: name (string) and age (integer).
A constructor method (__init__) that initializes the name and age attributes with the values passed as parameters.
Create two instances of the Person class with the following information:

Person 1: Name - "Alice", Age - 25
Person 2: Name - "Bob", Age - 30
Print the name and age of both persons.